Understanding your business











Michelle Jackson
Joined Air Products: 1990
Based: Crewe,   UK
Background: Previously worked in the hotel and  catering sector, prior to entering the gas industry as a food market specialist
Contact: jacksomc@airproducts.com






About Michelle 
Since joining Air Products as a market specialist,  Michelle has helped many food manufacturers and processors to realise the  benefits of using gas mixtures to improve the shelf-life or enhance the appeal  of specific food groups. During the past decade, take up of Modified Atmosphere  Packaging (MAP) in the UK  has soared.    
In her current role as European MAP specialist,  Michelle is a recognised industry expert; up-to-date with the latest trends and  technologies. As well as advising companies on MAP solutions, she provides  onsite training in how to use MAP to a wide range of food businesses and  packaging machinery companies. She is also a focal point for MAP training  within Air Products.    
Her experience 
Michelle has a wealth of experience in the food sector  as a MAP specialist and all her knowledge about how gases react with different  food groups has been included in Air Products’ MAP handbook – a highly-valued  industry resource.    
During the course of her career, she has particularly enjoyed  working closely with food businesses of all sizes – from cottage industries and  farm shops to leading food producers - to support their growth plans. As well  as advising on MAP solutions, she likes to explain how complementary freezing  and chilling systems can also be used.    
In the future, she aims to apply her knowledge and  experience to food businesses across Europe,  where the MAP marketplace is still developing.    
On a  personal note… 
Michelle is a true foodie who loves tasting and  cooking food from all corners of the world. Appreciative of fine-dining,  Michelle also enjoys nothing more than bringing back a recipe of a dish she has  tried on holiday and cooking it for her family.  
Interview with Michelle
























